description: Stacy Lane Dad passed away last Thursday afternoon after a 7-week struggle with lung cancer that returned after three years.  Even though he was 91 and lived a good long life, it will be so hard to say good-bye to him tomorrow.  I know part of him died when mom died last year, but he continued on living his life like he wanted -- fiercely independent til the end.  He became a bigger part of our family when he moved to Dublin, and I know Cathy and all of my kids cherish the time we had with him this last year. He was ready to go and be with his Lord and ready to see mom again.  I'm sure they will have a beautiful reunion.  I am thankful for the hope of heaven and grateful that God gave me and my brorthers a godly father to lead us while on this earth.  Rest in peace, Dad.  We love you more, and we'll see you in a little while. Stacy Lane Stacy Lane
